{
  "enabled": false,
  "qualityTarget": "realistic-singapore-mobile",
  "notes": [
    "Realistic-style pivot (2026-07-21): assets come from Objaverse (CC-licensed",
    "Sketchfab uploads), fetched + license-filtered via tools/objaverse_fetch.py -",
    "see objaverseAssets below for the real, populated entries with license/author.",
    "The old environment/locationModels/prefabs fields (Unity-Asset-Store-shaped,",
    "pointed at files that never existed) have been removed entirely - they were",
    "never the live asset-swap mechanism anyway (life-sim.js's",
    "loadDistrictAssetSamples() is, and always runs regardless of this manifest).",
    "",
    "character (Phase 2 finding): Objaverse's whole 'person' LVIS category is",
    "only 78 objects, almost all static scans/art busts, not rigged game",
    "characters. Exactly one license-eligible candidate had 2+ baked animations",
    "(12, in fact) - but they were VTuber calibration/gesture clips (Head",
    "Calibration, Dance, Explain1/2, Surprised), zero locomotion, so it can't",
    "drive idle/walk/run for this game. Objaverse is not a good source for this",
    "specific asset. Mixamo (free, Adobe, purpose-built for idle/walk/run/jump/",
    "sit/eat/exercise rigged clips) is the standard fit here, but requires a",
    "manual download through their web app (no scriptable API, login-gated) -",
    "a human needs to pick a character + clips and drop the exported GLBs into",
    "assets/characters/ + assets/characters/animations/ before this can be",
    "populated for real. Left null below until that happens; the live game",
    "keeps using the primitive capsule/sphere rig (createPlayer() in",
    "life-sim.js) in the meantime - loadCharacterAsset() just returns false",
    "when character is null, no crash, no broken state.",
    "",
    "Keep total first-load model + texture size under 45MB for mobile."
  ],
